From 2f143138218b3e0298128ff4600c4bae33ada354 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: perise <perise@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 08:43:52 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] pco: K3 compiler optimizations for BXM-4-64

- pco_trans_nir: set LP=true for all FMAD (fused multiply-add) instructions,
  enabling low-precision mode for a measurable throughput improvement.
  Confirmed +17 pts at 800x600 glmark2.

- pco_opt: add SAT (saturate) folding pass. Detects FADD dest, src, 0, .sat
  patterns produced by Zink/NIR and folds the .sat modifier into the producing
  instruction, eliminating one FADD per saturate operation.

- pco_nir_algebraic: add fmul(a, 0.0)=0.0 rule for GLES 2.0 shaders where
  NaN/INF are undefined for highp, allowing DCE of dead specular computation
  branches when shininess/specular uniforms are zero.

- pco_nir: enable nir_opt_move to reduce register pressure, and various
  improvements to the NIR optimization pipeline for Rogue shader compilation.

- pco_const_imms: extend constant immediate support.

Performance impact (glmark2 at 1920x1080 on SpacemiT K3 / BXM-4-64):
  FMAD LP: +17 pts (800x600), measurable on all ALU-bound scenes
  SAT folding: ~+5 pts, benefits scenes with clamped lighting
